correctness.rationale: Largely incorrect and not traceable to the article, with multiple schema and factual issues. Key problems: (1) Many values are fabricated/not reported in the paper: optical properties (refractive index, absorption, band gap and Tauc method), uniformity, conformality, roughness, film density, detailed film composition (50%/50% and Zn:O=1:1 via SIMS), deviceProperties (all TFT metrics). None are present in the article. (2) Wrong units/values: dosingTime and purgeTime are 5 s and 15 s in the article but encoded as 5 ms and 15 ms; should be 5000 ms and 15000 ms. Growth per cycle is ~0.14 nm/cycle (DMeZn) and ~0.13 nm/cycle (DEtZn); extraction uses 0.14 Å and 0.13 Å (10× too small). Pressure is given as 5×10^-6 Pa (base pressure) in the article; extraction uses 5e-06 mmHg (wrong unit and value). (3) PurgingGas: article states purging by evacuation (pump), not N2 purge; setting “high purity nitrogen” is incorrect. (4) Temperature: article investigated 90–270 °C; 120 °C (DMeZn) and 130 °C (DEtZn) are ALD-window onsets, not specific deposition temperatures tied to the reported film properties; binding a single T to each process is misleading. (5) NucleationPeriod (10 cycles) is not reported. (6) Flow rates (10 sccm/50 sccm) are not provided in the article. (7) plasmaPower set to null violates the schema (if unused, the field should be omitted). (8) Film thickness values (28 nm, 39 nm) are implied by cycles×GPC but not explicitly reported and depend on T; acceptable only if clearly derived and consistent with the correct GPC units (currently inconsistent due to Å vs nm error). Corrections needed: remove unreported properties or ground them to the text; fix dosing times to ms equivalents; correct GPC to 1.4 Å and 1.3 Å (or 0.14/0.13 nm); correct pressure (convert 5×10^-6 Pa to ≈3.75×10^-8 mmHg if using mmHg) and note this is base pressure; set purgingGas to reflect evacuation; omit plasmaPower; avoid inventing flow rates, composition ratios, optical/device metrics.

completeness.rationale: Many fields are untraceable to the article, several units/values are incorrect, and there are schema issues. Key problems: (1) Fabricated properties not reported in the paper: optical properties (n, absorption, band gap), uniformity, conformality, roughness, film density, elemental concentration and Zn:O atomic ratio (SIMS was used only for C and H impurities), device/TFT metrics (no devices were made), flow rates (not given), nucleation period (not given), and film thickness roughness/density values. These should be omitted or clearly grounded; the article does not provide them. (2) Unit and value errors: growth-per-cycle is reported as ~0.14 nm (DMeZn) and ~0.13 nm (DEtZn); the extraction uses 0.14 and 0.13 with ANGSTROM units (10× too small). Dosing/purge times were 5 s and 15 s; the schema unit is milliseconds—values should be 5000 ms and 15000 ms, not 5 ms and 15 ms. Pressure: the article states base pressure 5×10^-6 Pa; the extraction gives 5×10^-6 mmHg and uses it as deposition pressure—both the unit conversion and the meaning (base vs deposition pressure) are incorrect. (3) Process misinterpretations: purging was by evacuation, not by nitrogen purge; setting purgingGas to N2 is inaccurate. (4) Schema issues: plasmaPower is set to null (should be omitted if not used); several numeric fields are present with invented values, violating traceability. (5) Scope: the study spans 90–270 °C with two precursors; only two single-temperature instances are captured and much of the reported temperature-dependent behavior (e.g., ALD windows at 120–170 °C and 130–170 °C) is not represented; however, this is secondary to the larger accuracy issues. Properties to add/review: correct GPC units (use ~1.4 Å and ~1.3 Å), correct dosing/purge times (5000/15000 ms), correct pressure (convert 5×10^-6 Pa to Torr if used, and clarify base vs deposition), set purging to evacuation (not N2), remove null plasmaPower, remove or leave unspecified all unreported properties (flow rates, optical/device/roughness/density/uniformity/conformality/composition, nucleation period) or replace with values explicitly provided (e.g., include qualitative/quantitative XRD and the specific Hall mobility examples only if precisely cited).
